p: TDR levels were determined from the 67 sequenced samples. Four specimens (6.0%) carried major DRMs, corresponding to a moderate TDR level [ 60]. Two had K103N, one G190S and one Y181C, all representing resistance to non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitors (NNRTI). No NRTI or protease inhibitor (PI) associated DRMs were identified among the sequenced samples ( Table 1). Although there were more females enrolled in the survey than men there were no association between gender and DRMs (2 men and 2 females carried HIVDR virus; p = 0.084, FET).
